    "content_hash": "b7e063dffae6d484",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Loot Labs is on a mission to make collecting fun. We believe that every collectible tells a story: of passion, nostalgia, and discovery.\n\nThrough our flagship product, Boxed.gg http://Boxed.gg we are reimagining how the world collects by blending digital entertainment with tangible rewards, delivering nostalgia and discovery straight to the fans' doorsteps.\n\nWe are...\n\n - Community First: We've served 500k collectors and foster an active community of over 125k+ Discord members.\n\n - Ambitiously Led: Led by veterans from Microsoft, Twitch, 2K, and Boeing.\n\n - Remote-First: We value high autonomy, low ego, and trust our team to build from anywhere in the world.\n\nSince our inception in 2023, we’ve seen significant year-over-year growth. And now we're gearing up for our most ambitious year yet, with major expansions planned across product offerings, strategic partnerships, and next-generation collector experiences. If you’re ready to build products that spark joy at a global scale, you’re in the right place.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nWe’re hiring a Senior Full Stack Engineer (Frontend Leaning) who can own polished, performant user interfaces end-to-end from design implementation to delivery. This role is for engineers who care about the details, ship quickly without sacrificing quality, and thrive in high-trust, high-ownership environments.\n\nLocation: Remote (North America preferred) Occasional U.S. travel is required for in-person collaboration, team offsites, and company events.\n\nType: Full-time\n\nTime Zone Requirement: Must have 5+ hours of overlap with US Pacific Time (9am–6pm PT)\n\nLanguage: Must be fluent in English and comfortable working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment\n\n\n\nWHY YOU’LL LOVE WORKING HERE\n\n - You’ll own features end-to-end and see your impact in days, not months.\n\n - Work alongside people who ship fast and care about the details.\n\n - Take ownership in ambiguous situations and shape solutions collaboratively.\n\n\nHOW YOU’LL CONTRIBUTE \u0026 SUCCEED HERE\n\n - Bring senior-level experience building production frontend systems (typically 5+ years)\n\n - Build high-quality web applications using Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and GraphQL\n\n - Translate Figma designs into polished, responsive interfaces that match design intent across devices\n\n - Architect and manage complex state and data flows in React (Zustand, SWR, or similar)\n\n - Optimize for performance, rendering efficiency, SEO, and Core Web Vitals\n\n - Own features from planning through launch, monitoring, and iteration\n\n - Collaborate with backend, design, and product to deliver seamless features aligned with user needs and product goals\n\n - Balance speed and quality, knowing when to ship and when to refine\n\n - Bring strong product sense and user empathy. Always build with the why in mind, not just the what\n\n - Proactively communicate, raise concerns early, and collaborate openly with teammates to solve problems.\n\n - Mentor others, share knowledge, and help raise the technical bar.\n\n\nBONUS SKILLS\n\n - Experience with design systems, animation, or advanced UX work\n\n - Ability to contribute effectively to backend work (Node.js, AWS, GraphQL) when needed\n\n - Experience implementing and validating analytics or event tracking\n\n - Familiarity with payment flows or e-commerce systems\n\n - Experience building mobile apps\n\n - Interest in collectibles, gaming, or creator platforms\n   \n\nWorking Hours \u0026 Compensation\n\nLoot Labs is a remote-first company, and this role is open to candidates globally. To support efficient collaboration across teams, we will prioritize applicants who have working hour overlap with U.S. and E.U. time zones.\n\nCompensation will be competitive and based on your experience level as well as local market benchmarks for your region.\n\nAccessibility \u0026 Employment Eligibility\n\nWe are committed to providing an inclusive and accessible recruitment process. If you need any accommodations during the application or interview process, please let us know—we’re happy to support you.\n\nFor candidates located in the United States: Loot Labs participates in E-Verify and will confirm work authorization as part of the hiring process.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
